    <date day="27" month="April" year="2019"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>   A rejected Erratum to RFC4291 "IPv6 Addr Archi" on the topic of link-
   local addresses 'would need' a draft.  This is an answer to that
   need.

   The length of the prefix of an IPv6 link-local address is variable.
   The minimal value is 10 decimal.  The maximum value is 127 decimal.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
